From Glynne Tolar Subject Re Laser vs Bubblejet In article writes There is one wild difference between the two printers a laserprinter is a page printer whilst an inkjet is a line This means that a laserprinter can rotate graphic images whilst an inkjet Few drivers actually use this there is also the matter of downloadable fonts and so on E mail or I have a DeskJet and I thought I'd give a little The DeskJet WILL do landscape mode like the HP I can't say if other inkjets do Also the DeskJet can do downloadable fonts ONLY if you buy a softfont memory cart for OH You said the LaserJet can rotate a graphic image Hmmmmm The DeskJet can only rotate Nevermind